<div class="container">
  <header class="header">
    <div class="header-text">
        <%= link_to '/' do %>
        <h1>Matt Villwock | Web Developer</h1>
        <% end %>
        <p>What dream can I help you build?</p>
        <h2></h2>
    </div>
<!-- <div class="hr"></div> -->
  </header>

  <%= render 'nav' %>

  <div class="hr" id="summary"></div>
  <!-- start main content -->
  <div class="main-content">
    <div class="summary">
      <h3>About Me</h3>
      <p>Hi, my name is Matt. I'm a web developer, and a recent graduate of <%= link_to 'http://devbootcamp.com/', target: "_blank" do %>Dev Bootcamp <% end %>. I came to web development after getting a taste of it in digital marketing and getting hooked on building things.</p>
      <p>This is my personal website and blog, built using the <%= link_to 'https://github.com/rails/rails', target: "_blank" do %>Ruby on Rails <% end %> web framework. Listed below are my projects, along with links to contact me.</p>
      <p>I love building things, working in teams, and solving problems.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="hr" id="project-list"></div>

    <div class="project-list">

      <div class="project" id="hummingbird">

        <%= link_to 'https://github.com/jeremymcintyre/hummingbird', target: "_blank" do %>
        <%= image_tag('hummingbird-small.png', :class => "hummingbird", :alt => "hummingbird") %>
        <% end %>

        <div class="project-description">
          <h3>Hummingbird</h3>
          <p>Hummingbird was my final project at Dev Bootcamp. </p>
          <p>The app allows users to schedule text messages to be delivered at a more optimal time. </p>
          <p>Our team built the app in seven days, using a Ruby on Rails API back-end with an <%= link_to 'http://ionicframework.com/', target: "_blank" do %>Ionic<% end %> and <%= link_to 'https://angularjs.org/', target: "_blank" do %>Angular.js<% end %> front-end.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hr"></div>

      <div class="project" id="maps">

        <%= link_to 'https:/github.com/mtvillwock/maps-with-friends', target: "_blank" do %>
        <%= image_tag('maps-with-friends.jpg', :class => "maps-image", :alt => "maps with friends") %>
        <% end %>

        <div class="project-description">
          <h3>Maps with Friends</h3>
          <p>Maps With Friends is a side project I am working on during my job search after graduating from Dev Bootcamp. </p>
          <p>A conversation with a friend from high school gave me the idea to build something that would allow me to visualize the diverse locations where my friends had scattered across the country. </p>
          <p>Technologies used include <%= link_to 'http://www.sinatrarb.com/', target: "_blank" do %>Sinatra
            <% end %>, JavaScript, and the <%= link_to 'https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/', target: "_blank" do %>Google Maps API<% end %>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hr"></div>

      <div class="project" id="pending">

        <%= link_to '#' do %>
        <%= image_tag("geocode.jpg", :class => "pending", :alt => "pending project") %>
        <% end %>

        <div class="project-description">
          <h3>Project To Be</h3>
          <p>What can I help you build?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hr"></div>

    <div class="about">
      <p>Content Here</p>
    </div>

    <div class="hr"></div>

    <div class="contact">
      <h3>Contact Me | Collaborate</h3>
      <p>API, web app, or landing page â€“ I can help you realize your vision. <%= link_to "mailto:" + ENV["ADMIN_EMAIL"], target: "_blank" do %>Contact me<% end %> and we can discuss building your dream.</p>
      <p>If you're a fellow developer who wants to work on a project, <%= link_to "mailto:" + ENV["ADMIN_EMAIL"], target: "_blank" do %>shoot me an email<% end %> and tell me all about it. I'm always looking for opportunities to help other people.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- End main content -->
  <div class="hr"></div>

  <%= render 'nav' %>

  <div class="hr"></div>
</div>

